{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Add focused prerequisite consistency review\n\n## Goal\nEvaluate whether a ticket's plan remains consistent with each direct prerequisite without injecting prerequisite material into every general reviewer or changing existing parent/child review behavior.\n\n## Implementation\n- Register a specialized criterion that triggers only after PlanRelationSnapshot collection succeeds and direct prerequisites exist. Unreadable/unresolvable targets stop earlier in pin collection; indeterminate is reserved for readable pinned targets with failed evaluation or attribution.\n- Consume the pin story's PlanRelationSnapshot contract; use it only to construct isolated specialized-criterion inputs. Never inject prerequisite material into general finder/verifier calls. Add an integration test proving pin collection plus criterion routing share one preload without prompt leakage.\n- Batch multiple independent subject-to-prerequisite evaluations when whole prerequisite blocks fit within the existing context headroom. Never split the subject or a prerequisite.\n- Require exactly one record {prerequisite_id, disposition, findings} per readable pinned canonical ID. disposition is consistent, finding, or indeterminate. consistent has no findings; finding has findings attributed to that ID; indeterminate requires reason_code exactly evaluation-error, output-invalid, or attribution-invalid plus optional diagnostic detail, and cannot assert incompatibility. Any indeterminate, missing, duplicate, unknown-ID, or malformed record makes the review unsigned INDETERMINATE because certification requires complete coverage.\n- Keep batching semantically neutral: do not create cross-prerequisite findings whose availability depends on bin membership.\n- Extend the existing finding schema with optional prerequisite_id and the index-keyed Pass 2 binary schema with optional prerequisite_attribution_valid=yes|no|na. Pass 2 sets yes only for the indexed finding's exact in-bin canonical ID. Pass 3 preserves IDs on upheld findings, drops attribution=no as unsupported, and makes missing/malformed verification unsigned INDETERMINATE. Reuse the phase story's threshold function; do not add a separate decide pipeline.\n- Pre-pack with sizing.container_budget(). On sizing.is_context_limit_error(), split the failing stable-order bin into contiguous halves recursively. A singleton escalates through models_at_or_above(); failure at the largest window produces too-large remediation. Non-context errors produce unsigned INDETERMINATE.\n- Extend fidelity_spot_eval.packing_spot_eval and parity.container_fidelity_report with at least eight gold prerequisite sets, each containing at least three prerequisites: two all-consistent, two single-conflict, two tail-conflict, one attribution-confusion, and one multi-bin case. Compute finding recall plus false acceptance against one-per-call; packed recall may not decrease, false acceptance may not increase, coverage must be complete, and corpus-wide attribution errors must be zero. Failure retains smaller bins or one-per-call.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Only the focused criterion receives prerequisite material; general criteria and all existing parent/child handling remain unchanged.\n- [ ] Token-budget batching never splits the subject or a prerequisite.\n- [ ] Every readable pinned prerequisite receives exactly one coverage disposition.\n- [ ] Missing or incorrect canonical-ID attribution cannot produce a blocking finding.\n- [ ] Every finding upheld from Pass 3 carries a Pass-2-verified prerequisite_id matching the source prerequisite canonical ID.\n- [ ] Indeterminate records use only the closed reason_code enum and remain unsigned.\n- [ ] Deterministic tests cover Pass-2 verification, smaller-bin fallback, and oversized remediation.\n- [ ] The established opt-in live evaluation proves packed fidelity meets the one-per-call contract.\n\n## Verification\n- Run focused registry, Pass-1/Pass-2, sizing, and fidelity spot-eval tests.\n- Run the existing opt-in prerequisite fidelity evaluation and record its result on the ticket.\n- Run make check and the non-integration test suite.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784526328944017001,"uuid":"5f19011c-df10-4acd-a49f-9adc1f8b0925"}